				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have to agree with the comments on Agility, I wasn't aware of the threshold of 75 but I can agree that my default of 70 was not enough.  I can't comment quantitatively on the AC issues but I can on speed.
<br />

<br />
I created my Erudite Mage using an identical chart of stats from Casters Realm <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />  During my lowbie days, I heard RL friends talking about running to zone/guards but I wondered how they did it cos I always got caught quickly and beaten down.
<br />

<br />
It was only when I created a dark elf character that I was alerted to the fact that the dark elf could run across half the zone back to Neriak with a whole train in tow.  I realised something was definately wrong with my erudite.  After I had acquired a few AGI items my Erudite found a new lease of life, literally.
<br />

<br />
With low agility you will not be able to outrun anything, well maybe golems in The Grey but that's little comfort to a newbie!<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=274972">Chard</a>, Arch Convoker <a href="http://www.berthall.com/">Bertoxxulous Server</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
