				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I took a very non-traditional view when I created Ark.  When I created my first mage, I put 25 points into STR.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="Laughing" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="Laughing" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I deleted him at level 6.
<br />

<br />
When I created Ark, I put 5 into STR, and the rest into AGI and STA.
<br />

<br />
At low levels this made him a LOT tougher than other newbs. And at my current level, I have five slots with no INT in them and still have my INT at 250+.  I have higher AC and HPs than many INT casters my level.
<br />

<br />
My wife and I did notice the relationship of run to AGI.  There is another factor here, though.  I think it is either total weight (NOT encumbered) or excess carrying capacity.  Because with the same AGI I can outrun her even thought she is not encumbered.   But I carry less (total) and have more free carying capacity than she does.  Or, maybe it's an amor thing...  Anyway we tried it naked and she keeps up just fine, so it's definitely some kind of equipment/load relationship.<br />_________________<br />[url=pub86.ezboard.com/bveterancrew]<img src="http://home.swbell.net/mkswet/ark_sig2.jpg" border="0" />[/url]
<br />
